<TABLE CLASS="SPELLS" WIDTH=100%>
<TR><TH>actually...<BR>
<I><FONT SIZE=-1>Posted 2000-03-15 16:16:37 by Gohankun of Tarew Marr</FONT></I></TH></TR>
<TR><TD>This is an area of effect spell and is not meant for in-combat usage if you are being hit. If you can pull it off, then great, but it is best used for multiple creatures in a small radius. Lets say 3 creatures attacking one or two PCs together; target the center creature and cast Invoke Lightning, ALL the creatures will be struck with lightning. As for fighting a single creature, this is not a very mana efficient spell because around level 5, you can't throw around 32Mana like you can a full rank later (plus you don't have meditate until lvl 8) Just my opinion :o)</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<BR>
<TABLE CLASS="SPELLS" WIDTH=100%>
<TR><TH>Use<BR>
<I><FONT SIZE=-1>Posted 2000-03-10 01:50:19 by Salamonius</FONT></I></TH></TR>
<TR><TD>Actually the best way to use this spell is at the start of the battle, hit the enemy with either Snare or Grasping Roots, Grasping Roots if you can since that'll do 10 dmg to them.  After that hit them with Invoke Lightning, they'll be hit with the entire spell away from you so you won't take any damage either and it damages them more.  Then you can keep casting at them till you're out of mana or the root breaks and they come at you or you can just go in and melee them and save your mana for healing yourself if you need it.  Hope that helps.</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
